org.concordion.cubano.driver.web.pagefactory

Class PageObjectAwareHtmlElementsLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.concordion.cubano.driver.web.pagefactory.PageObjectAwareHtmlElementsLoader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.openqa.selenium.internal.WrapsDriver

    public class PageObjectAwareHtmlElementsLoader
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.openqa.selenium.internal.WrapsDriver

    A helper class for finding custom HtmlElement(s) in the same way that driver.findElement() and driver.findElements() methods work.

    TODO It needs to pass correct decorator - see TODO on PageObjectAwareHtmlElementDecorator.

      • findElements

        public <T extends ru.yandex.qatools.htmlelements.element.HtmlElement> java.util.List<T> findElements(java.lang.Class<T> elementClass,
                                                                                                     org.openqa.selenium.By by)

        Find all elements within the current page using the given mechanism. This method is affected by the ‘implicit wait’ times in force at the time of execution. When implicitly waiting, this method will return as soon as there are more than 0 items in the found collection, or will return an empty list if the timeout is reached.

        Type Parameters:
        T - A class that extends HtmlElement
        Parameters:
        elementClass - The specific HtmlElement class wrapping the element
        by - The locating mechanism to use
        Returns:
        A list of all WebElements, or an empty list if nothing matches
        See Also:
        By, WebDriver.Timeouts

      • findElement

        public <T extends ru.yandex.qatools.htmlelements.element.HtmlElement> T findElement(java.lang.Class<T> elementClass,
                                                                                    org.openqa.selenium.By by)

        Find the first WebElement using the given method. This method is affected by the ‘implicit wait’ times in force at the time of execution. The findElement(..) invocation will return a matching row, or try again repeatedly until the configured timeout is reached.

        findElement should not be used to look for non-present elements, use WebDriver.findElements(By) and assert zero length response instead.

        Type Parameters:
        T - A class that extends HtmlElement
        Parameters:
        elementClass - The specific HtmlElement class wrapping the element
        by - The locating mechanism
        Returns:
        The first matching element on the current page
        Throws:
        org.openqa.selenium.NoSuchElementException - If no matching elements are found
        See Also:
        By, WebDriver.Timeouts

      • createHtmlElement

        public static <T extends ru.yandex.qatools.htmlelements.element.HtmlElement> T createHtmlElement(java.lang.Class<T> elementClass,
                                                                                                 org.openqa.selenium.WebElement elementToWrap,
                                                                                                 java.lang.String name,
                                                                                                 BasePageObject<?> parentPageObject)

        Creates an instance of the given class representing a block of elements and initializes its fields with lazy proxies.

        Is a COPY of the Yandex HtmlElementLoader classes method so can replace the call to populatePageObject() with one that supports our page decorator AND set the page object if required.

        Type Parameters:
        T - A class to be instantiated and initialized.
        Parameters:
        elementClass - A class to be instantiated and initialized.
        elementToWrap - WebElement to wrap
        name - Name of element
        parentPageObject - PageObject sitting on
        Returns:
        Initialised instance of the specified class.
